{'job_titles': 'Test engineer | Industrial IoT technology | Artificial Intelligence| Eindhoven | Salary up to €60k', 'job_description': 'The organization

This organization is located on the High-Tech Campus in Eindhoven and can be described as an innovator in the industry. They use the most modern technology possible to come up with advanced IoT sensor systems in combination with data analytics to help industrial companies eliminate unplanned downtime and lengthen the lifetime of their assets. The technology this organization provides helps industrial operations become more sustainable and effective.

An example of such a project is a sensor that this organization has developed for the entire train rail network in Sweden and Germany. With the use of these sensors, the end clients could gather all significant data in order to analyze the status of the rails, but also to measure the effect of the speed and weight a train has on the rails. All data gathered can help the company measure and detect early traces of wear on the rails and give them the opportunity to act quickly.

Function and Team

You strive for high customer satisfaction by constantly looking for ways to improve the customer experience. You also know how to explain complex situations clearly and simply to customers. With this you know how to build a good and long-term relationship with our customers.

As the role of Tester and Field Application Engineer is new to Sensorfy, you will be a pioneer in this field. You love this challenge and enjoy the freedom and flexibility it offers you.

Because you are part of the development department, you are a real team player with an open attitude, a positive attitude and a high degree of personal responsibility. You function well in a global and rapidly changing environment where your ability to prioritize – and re-prioritize – comes into its own.

Requirements
Obtained your Bachelor- or Master’s degree;
Linux skills;
Some knowledge of IoT
Python;
Good communication skills in English, Dutch is a plus;
Conditions
Salary up to 60k;
Travelling costs reimbursed;
26 vacation days;
Flexibility in working hours;
Working hybrid possible;
Opportunity to gain stock;
Interested?

 Julia@layer.nl
 06 – 82 45 68 44', 'images': 'https://media.glassdoor.com/sql/758990/layer-squarelogo-1438288181957.png', 'locations': 'Eindhoven', 'salaries': '€60K (Employer est.)', 'companies': 'Layer', 'pros': '["In my past I had a chance to work at big companies, small ones, well established companies and start-ups — either the teams were too big and cumbersome, ruined by bureaucracy, or too small and naive to make a dent in the industry. I was just trying to find the sweet-spot and I think I found it at Layer. In my career I've never grown so fast as I did here. I have the chance to work and help invent great technologies and an opportunity to grow. It's where I always have a chance to be heard and make an impact — everything that was difficult to achieve in my previous employments. The product we're building keeps getting better and better, and it's so satisfying seeing the numbers grow as we deliver. Team is practically like a second family which has a nice mixture of introverts and extroverts, funny and intelligent people that I can always look up to. I don't think I'd want to be anywhere else.", 'Since the day I interviewed, I have been smiling from ear to ear. The people here are unbelievably nice and helpful. My first day I sat in on a meeting where the CEO, a potential customer, was so impressed with the product that he came in to find out what the problem was. The product is amazing. I feel lucky and grateful to be working here. We have catered lunch three days a week which is healthy and delicious.', "Layer has an amazing idea - power the communications in every mobile and web service. Everyone who hears the idea - customers, in particular - agrees and demand is off the charts.  Then there's the team.  I've never seen such phenomenal talent together on one team. It's early innings for this company, but the opportunity is massive.", 'A legit business idea with insane potential.  No shortage of technical challenges (if you don\'t see this as a "pro" then work elsewhere), all solvable.  Incredibly smart & talented team.  A "use the right tool for the job" mentality.', 'Nice office. \n\nClose to highways and train. \n\nCool crew (outside of executive team) to work with. \n\nLunch a few time a week.', 'Messaging is an interesting space, the pie is large, and there is not an industry leader in the US.', 'You can over-engineer anything.\r\nThe office is nice.', 'No one will use your work']', 'cons': '["There are a lot of other start-ups that share their well instituted business model. With Layer the territory we're in is relatively new, which makes it the kind of a company that has to make its own mistakes to learn and grow — which is sometimes scary, but exciting.", "I have, yet, to find issue, but I've only been here a month. I would love it if we had lunch catered 5 times a week but no need to shorten the runway for my gluttony.", 'Honestly and truly, this company is great.  The team is aligned toward a common goal.  There are no apparent cons.', "You can't build this overnight, and this work is not for the weary.  Do it because you love it.  This is not a 9-to-5 situation.", 'Over promise and under deliver. Ron rest on his past wins of being lucky with google voice and losing on OpendDNS. They sell you hard to bring you on board. \n\nMy tenure there we went through 4 VP of sales (one quit on day 5 once she realized what was going on). 3 VP of marketing... I can go in. \n\nRon decides to hire C players in hopes of them being A players. \n\nThey over sell their clients and cannot deliver on the vision. \n\nThey stole the VP from trunk club. Their only one real success story customer.', "You'll notice most of these reviews are from 2-3 years ago, when Layer was in its prime. The industry has passed Layer by unfortunately. There is very little transparency given it's only a company of 30 people. The executive turnover is very high, a sign of chaos at the top.", "Management doesn't listen to you.\r\nLack of direction/vision.\r\nNegative vibe in the office.\r\nInhumane attitude between coworkers.\r\nThey will burn you out (no concept of productivity, all that counts is # of hours).", 'Not trustworthy management, all positive reviews are fake']'}

{'job_titles': 'Machine Learning Engineer', 'job_description': 'max. € 5.088 ,- 36 uur wo bepaalde tijd
Wil jij je inzetten om de toepassing van AI in het ziekenhuis te laten slagen? Wil je aan de slag met medische data om innovatieve toepassingen te ontwikkelen voor in de kliniek? En wil jij samen met onze artsen en verpleegkundigen deze toepassingen effectief implementeren? Dan ben jij onze nieuwe machine learning engineer!
Wat ga je doen?
Als machine learning engineer is jouw hoofddoel de implementatie van waardevolle AI-modellen in de complexe architectuur van het ziekenhuis. Een deel van de AI-modellen zul je zelf ontwikkelen, maar je zult ook werken met modellen die al bestaan of in co-creatie worden gemaakt. Omdat deze modellen daadwerkelijk in de praktijk gebruikt moeten worden, bouw je mee aan een volwassen MLOps omgeving, met oplossingen voor datasetmanagement, on-premise deployment, experiment management en data en performance monitoring. De toepassingen die jij live zet zijn onderdeel van strategische innovaties in het ziekenhuis en hebben als doel het verbeteren van het zorgproces voor zowel zorgprofessionals als patiënten. Denk hierbij bijvoorbeeld aan het verlichten van de registratielast of vroegherkenning van verslechteringen bij patiënten. Uiteraard sta je er niet alleen voor: binnen deze functie werk je nauw samen met medisch specialisten en je collega’s met een achtergrond in de (technische) geneeskunde, econometrie, bewegingswetenschappen en artificial intelligence.
Wat neem je mee?
Je hebt een masteropleiding afgerond in de richting van data science, informatica of wiskunde;
Daarbij heb je aantoonbare werkervaring met machine learning modellen in productie brengen en heb je ervaring met programmeren in onder meer Python en SQL;
Verder ben je ervaren met MLOps en kan je requirements omzetten in een werkende infrastructuur in een hybride cloud-omgeving;
Kennis van en ervaring met NLP of Computer Vision is een pre;
Je bent enthousiast, gedreven en kunt goed schakelen tussen verschillende vakgebieden. Je kunt zelfstandig jouw projecten plannen en sturen en weet de verbinding te leggen tussen de techniek en de kliniek;
Tot slot ben je flexibel, heb je een innovatieve mindset en houd je van een uitdaging. Je ziet het als uitdaging om aan de slag te gaan binnen een groeiend en innoverend team dat nog beperkte structuren kent.
Waar ga je werken?
De afdeling Informatie Technologie & Digitale Innovatie (IT&DI) van het LUMC realiseert de link tussen de IT en de zorg. Wij staan in het hart van de organisatie en maken het leveren van topreferente zorg, internationaal onderzoek en academisch onderwijs mogelijk. Hierbij staan innovatie, het werken met de nieuwste technologie en kennisontwikkeling voorop. Je gaat aan de slag binnen het AI team. Hier werk je samen met zowel ontwikkelaars als onderzoekers op het gebied van AI. Ons jonge en enthousiaste team bestaat uit verschillende disciplines die gezamenlijk werken aan het toepassen van AI in de kliniek. Ook word je onderdeel van het CAIRELab; het kennis- en expertisecentrum voor kunstmatige intelligentie in de zorg van het LUMC.
Meer informatie
Voor deze vacature kunnen referenties worden opgevraagd.
Acquisitie naar aanleiding van deze vacature wordt niet op prijs gesteld.
Contact
Alexander van Someren – Senior Data Scientist, afdeling IT&DI
A.van_Someren@lumc.nl', 'images': 'https://media.glassdoor.com/sql/499589/leiden-university-medical-center-squarelogo-1426591944941.png', 'locations': 'Leiden', 'salaries': '€5K (Employer est.)', 'companies': 'LUMC', 'pros': "['relaxed, work life is great, helpful team', 'High tech facility\ncollective working environment, Lot of English speakers, Best of the scientific minds around.', 'Freedom in your own research and non-hierarchal culture.']", 'cons': "['boring, compensation could be better, work is all over the place', 'Nothing as such. Every place has some or the other minor cons.', 'Support during the COVID-19 time was poor compared to other university hospitals. Future career perspective of young academic staffs are not a concern for the management. Colleagues who are in phd/postdoc level got unfair contracts.']"}
